<subSubSection id="C37BF0C9D02EFFCEFF2D9E64B2E9FB84" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BDEA342D02EFFCEFF2D9E64B1DDFE2E" blockId="13.[151,678,366,388]" box="[151,678,366,388]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C61D8C1D02EFFCEFE9C9E65B134FE2E" box="[294,591,366,388]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Serridiocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="membranaceus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFE9C9E65B134FE2E" box="[294,591,366,388]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Serridiocerus membranaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFDEF9E64B1DDFE2E" bold="true" box="[597,678,367,388]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A226C22BD02EFFCEFDEF9E64B1DDFE2E" box="[597,678,367,388]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDEA342D02EFFCEFF2D9EBAB602FCA4" blockId="13.[151,1437,433,1501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
Body robust. Head wider than pronotum. Crown short with median length as long as length next to eyes, shagreen. Face wider than long; lateral frontal sutures present, curved, reaching ocelli; frontoclypeus and anteclypeus elevated, apex of frontoclypeus and base of anteclypeus broad; anteclypeus strongly convex, base wider than apex, surpassing apex of gena; lateral margin of gena concave in middle; lora narrow; ocelli placed closer to eyes than to each other; antenna aristiform, not expanded apically or subapically (
<figureCitation id="135ABFC7D02EFFCEFC6E9D4AB767FDF3" box="[980,1052,577,602]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,421,1289]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[162,1424,411,1296]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Serridiocerus membranaceus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male," httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264079/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
D). Pronotum shagreen, sparsely punctate, with short lateral margin, anterior margin convex, and posterior margin straight. Mesonotum and scutellum as long as pronotum and crown together (
<figureCitation id="135ABFC7D02EFFCEFCB39D82B029FD08" box="[777,850,649,674]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,421,1289]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[162,1424,411,1296]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Serridiocerus membranaceus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male," httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264079/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
C). Forewing with 4 apical and 2 subapical cells (crossveins absent, r-m1 and m-cu2 present), outer apical cell very large; appendix broad, extending to middle of 3rd apical cell (
<figureCitation id="135ABFC7D02EFFCEFEFE9DDAB2FDFD40" box="[324,390,721,746]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1317,1339]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,421,1289]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[162,1424,411,1296]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Serridiocerus membranaceus sp. nov. A, habitus of male, dorsal view; B, habitus of male, lateral view; C, head and thorax of male, dorsal view; D, face of male," httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264079/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
B). Fore femur with setae irregularly arranged and short. Fore tibia with several stout setae on apical half of AV and PV. Hind femur with 2+1 apical setae. Hind tibiae chaetotaxy PD 17–18, AD 6, AV 9–10.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDEA342D02EFFCEFF7D9C12B1F4FCFC" blockId="13.[151,1437,433,1501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
Male abdomen with pair of long tergal apodemes almost reaching entire length of sternite 5; sternal apodeme short, less than one segment long (
<figureCitation id="135ABFC7D02EFFCEFDA09C36B110FCFC" box="[538,619,829,854]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[190,1389,208,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[183,1398,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Serridiocerus membranaceus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, Forewing; E, abdominal apodemes; F, aedeagus, lateral view; G, aedeagus, ventral view; H, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264087/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDEA342D02EFFCEFF7D9C6AB2E9FB84" blockId="13.[151,1437,433,1501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
Male pygofer divided into short dorsal and long ventral section by horizontal membranous cleft; caudal margin with hooklike process (
<figureCitation id="135ABFC7D02EFFCEFE209C8EB290FC34" box="[410,491,901,926]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[190,1389,208,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[183,1398,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Serridiocerus membranaceus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, Forewing; E, abdominal apodemes; F, aedeagus, lateral view; G, aedeagus, ventral view; H, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264087/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
A). Segment X with elongate, finger-shaped ventrolateral extension. Subgenital plate slender, with short, sparse setae distally (
<figureCitation id="135ABFC7D02EFFCEFD329CA2B19AFC68" box="[648,737,937,962]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[190,1389,208,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[183,1398,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Serridiocerus membranaceus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, Forewing; E, abdominal apodemes; F, aedeagus, lateral view; G, aedeagus, ventral view; H, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264087/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
A). Style foot-shaped, curved dorsally with ventral margin produced; apical half tapering (
<figureCitation id="135ABFC7D02EFFCEFDBD9CC6B126FC4C" box="[519,605,973,998]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[190,1389,208,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[183,1398,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Serridiocerus membranaceus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, Forewing; E, abdominal apodemes; F, aedeagus, lateral view; G, aedeagus, ventral view; H, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264087/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
G). Connective T-shaped, with medial longitudinal keel (
<figureCitation id="135ABFC7D02EFFCEFB439CC6B623FC4C" box="[1273,1368,973,998]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[190,1389,208,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[183,1398,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Serridiocerus membranaceus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, Forewing; E, abdominal apodemes; F, aedeagus, lateral view; G, aedeagus, ventral view; H, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264087/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Figs. 16</figureCitation>
B–C). Aedeagal lateral margin serrate in apical half, dorsal and ventral apodemes well developed; gonopore on ventral surface (
<figureCitation id="135ABFC7D02EFFCEFF4D9B1EB229FB84" box="[247,338,1045,1070]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[190,1389,208,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[183,1398,193,1905]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Serridiocerus membranaceus sp. nov. A, male pygofer, anal tube and subgenital plate, lateral view; B, connective, ventral view; C, connective, lateral view; D, Forewing; E, abdominal apodemes; F, aedeagus, lateral view; G, aedeagus, ventral view; H, style, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264087/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Figs. 16</figureCitation>
E–F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37BF0C9D02EFFCEFF7D9B32B127FBF8" box="[199,604,1081,1106]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BDEA342D02EFFCEFF7D9B32B127FBF8" blockId="13.[151,1437,433,1501]" box="[199,604,1081,1106]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFF7D9B32B21BFBF8" bold="true" box="[199,352,1081,1106]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F376E3D2D02EFFCEFEDD9B32B2B5FBF8" box="[359,462,1081,1106]" name="Malaysia" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(Sandakan).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37BF0C9D02EFFCEFF7D9B56B06BFB30" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BDEA342D02EFFCEFF7D9B56B06BFB30" blockId="13.[151,1437,433,1501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFF7D9B56B235FBDC" bold="true" box="[199,334,1117,1142]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived by combining two words 
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFC7F9B55B08EFBDF" box="[965,1013,1118,1141]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Serr</emphasis>
-, referring to the lateral serrations of the aedeagus, with 
<taxonomicName id="4C61D8C1D02EFFCEFED79B8AB2ACFB33" box="[365,471,1153,1177]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idiocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFED79B8AB2ACFB33" box="[365,471,1153,1177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Idiocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="54DA1DE0D02EFFCEFDB49B89B145FB30" box="[526,574,1154,1178]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">type</typeStatus>
genus of the tribe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37BF0C9D02EFFCEFF7D9BAEB005FAE4" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDEA342D02EFFCEFF7D9BAEB005FAE4" blockId="13.[151,1437,433,1501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFF7D9BAEB23AFB14" bold="true" box="[199,321,1189,1214]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C61D8C1D02EFFCEFEF19BAEB298FB17" box="[331,483,1189,1213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Serridiocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFEF19BAEB298FB17" box="[331,483,1189,1213]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Serridiocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFE549BAEB121FB14" bold="true" box="[494,602,1189,1214]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A226C22BD02EFFCEFE549BAEB121FB14" box="[494,602,1189,1214]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be distinguished by its body brown; frontoclypeus and anteclypeus elevated, apex of frontoclypeus and base of anteclypeus broad; lora narrow; lateral frontal sutures curved, reaching corresponding ocelli; forewing with 2 subapical cells, outer apical cell largest; male pygofer with membranous on dorsum and medial and ventral area; style foot-shaped; aedeagal shaft serrate lateral margin, dorsal and ventral apodeme developed; gonopore situated an ventral margin apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37BF0C9D02EFFCEFF7D9A52B25EFA77" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDEA342D02EFFCEFF7D9A52B25EFA77" blockId="13.[151,1437,433,1501]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFF7D9A52B240FAD8" bold="true" box="[199,315,1369,1394]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C61D8C1D02EFFCEFEFC9A52B2A5FADB" box="[326,478,1369,1393]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Serridiocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFEFC9A52B2A5FADB" box="[326,478,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Serridiocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFE539A52B12CFAD8" bold="true" box="[489,599,1369,1394]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A226C22BD02EFFCEFE539A52B12CFAD8" box="[489,599,1369,1394]" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is distinguishable from other 
<taxonomicName id="4C61D8C1D02EFFCEFC009A52B743FAD8" box="[954,1080,1369,1394]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Idiocerinae">Idiocerinae</taxonomicName>
by the broad anteclypeus, the laterally serrate aedeagal shaft and presence of a ventral aedeagal apodeme. At present, the genus is known only from male specimens, but it seems likely that the structure of the lower part of the face is sexually dimorphic, as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C61D8C1D02EFFCEFF2D9ACDB265FA77" box="[151,286,1478,1501]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Namiocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="418" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9157F50D02EFFCEFF2D9ACDB265FA77" box="[151,286,1478,1501]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="418">Namiocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
